{
  "texts": [
    "No-vented fill operation did not succeed.",
    "Nevertheless, as buoyancy inhibits the vapor film formation, the authors suggest that on-orbit filling would promote the creation of the vapor layer at the wall, increasing the efficiency of the cool-down process.",
    "Propellant management devices (PMD) for cryogenic liquids were tested in compensated gravity conditions (TEXUS 48 Sounding Rocket) using liquid nitrogen by Behruzi et al.",
    "Different operations were tested: draining, refilling, heating, and depressurization.",
    "A successful operation could be demonstrated."
  ]
}